{
  "page": "Walys Mooton",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Mooton\" title=\"House Mooton\"><img alt=\"House Mooton.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a6/House_Mooton.svg/50px-House_Mooton.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a6/House_Mooton.svg/75px-House_Mooton.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a6/House_Mooton.svg/100px-House_Mooton.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Walys Mooton</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Mooton\" title=\"House Mooton\"><img alt=\"House Mooton.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a6/House_Mooton.svg/50px-House_Mooton.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a6/House_Mooton.svg/75px-House_Mooton.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a6/House_Mooton.svg/100px-House_Mooton.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Maidenpool\" title=\"Lord of Maidenpool\">Lord of Maidenpool</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Mooton\" title=\"House Mooton\">House Mooton</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">Blacks</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/130_AC\" title=\"130 AC\">130&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Rook&#39;s Rest\">Rook's Rest</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Played by</span></th><td>\nRichard Riddell</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>: <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_3\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 3\">Season 3</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Walys Mooton</b> was the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenpool\" title=\"Maidenpool\">Maidenpool</a> and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mooton\" title=\"House Mooton\">House Mooton</a> during the early part of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>, a character named Ser Walys Mooton will be portrayed by Richard Riddell.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Walys_Mooton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Following the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_Rook%27s_Rest\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Battle of Rook&#39;s Rest\">battle of Rook's Rest</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, Lord Walys desired to <a href=\"/index.php/Retaking_of_Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Retaking of Rook&#39;s Rest\">recover</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Rook&#39;s Rest\">Rook's Rest</a> for the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a> and Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>. Walys led a hundred <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenpool\" title=\"Maidenpool\">Maidenpool</a> and joined with soldiers from the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Crabb\" title=\"House Crabb\">Crabbs</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Brune_of_the_Dyre_Den\" title=\"House Brune of the Dyre Den\">Brunes</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Celtigar\" title=\"House Celtigar\">Celtigars</a>. They took the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a>' garrison at Rook's Rest by surprise and recovered the castle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Afterwards, Walys led his bravest soldiers to the field west of Rook's Rest to kill the injured <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a>. The attackers failed to kill the dragon, however. Three score were killed, including the charred Lord Walys, before the survivors fled. Walys was succeeded as Lord of Maidenpool by his brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Mooton\" title=\"Manfryd Mooton\">Manfryd Mooton</a>, who found Walys's body when he arrived at the castle a fortnight later.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Walys_Mooton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Walys and his brothers could be the children of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jonah_Mooton\" title=\"Jonah Mooton\">Jonah Mooton</a> and his lady wife, <a href=\"/index.php/Perianne_Moore\" title=\"Perianne Moore\">Perianne Moore</a>, who are known to have had a successful <a href=\"/index.php/Marriage\" title=\"Marriage\">marriage</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td 